description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Haematology Specialist Nurse – Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oxford University Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Haematology team are seeking a motivated and enthusiastic nurse to join their specialist nursing team. A new service has been set up for the Oxfordshire area (OxCom). This has been developed to ensure the safe and consistent management of patients within the MGUS and CLL services that are predominantly managed in the community. This is an exciting opportunity to contribute to the development of a new service whilst offering specialty advice and care to the patients on these pathways. You will work closely with OUH services and specialist clinical teams in Myeloma and CLL to triage and assign patients into the appropriate pathway for disease monitoring. Liaison with primary care services will also be key to the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have haematology nursing experience or experience in managing patients who require chronic condition monitoring and you are interested in the development, audit and evaluation of a new service we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Rachel Miller (Deputy Matron for Oncology and Haematology) for further information or to arrange an informal visit/discussion: rachel.miller@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Closinfg Date:10th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Rachel Miller (Deputy Matron for Oncology and Haematology) for further information or to arrange an informal visit/discussion: rachel.miller@ouh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
